intellectual.中释: 知识分子；凭理智做事者
intellectual.英释: an intelligent, well-educated person who spends time thinking about complicated ideas and discussing them

productivity.中释: 生产力；生产率；生产能力
productivity.英释: the rate at which goods are produced, and the amount produced, especially in relation to the work, time, and money needed to produce them

organization.英释: a group such as a club or business that has formed for a particular purpose

relationship.英释: the way in which two people or two groups feel about each other and behave towards each other

professional.英释: someone who earns money by doing a job, sport, or activity that many other people do just for fun

increasingly.英释: more and more all the time

conservative.英释: someone who supports or is a member of the Conservative Party in Britain

characterize.中释: 描绘…的特性；具有…的特征
characterize.英释: to describe the qualities of someone or something in a particular way

conservation.英释: the protection of natural things such as animals, plants, forests etc, to prevent them from being spoiled or destroyed

conventional.中释: 符合习俗的，传统的；常见的；惯例的
conventional.英释: a conventional method, product, practice etc has been used for a long time and is considered the usual type

significance.英释: The significance of something is the importance that it has, usually because it will have an effect on a situation or shows something about a situation

constitution.中释: 宪法；体制；章程；构造；建立，组成；体格
constitution.英释: a set of basic laws and principles that a country or organization is governed by

enthusiastic.英释: feeling or showing a lot of interest and excitement about something

considerable.中释: 相当大的；重要的，值得考虑的
considerable.英释: fairly large, especially large enough to have an effect or be important

unemployment.英释: the number of people in a particular country or area who cannot get a job

construction.英释: the process of building things such as houses, bridges, roads etc

architecture.中释: 建筑学；建筑风格；建筑式样；架构
architecture.英释: the style and design of a building or buildings

contribution.英释: something that you give or do in order to help something be successful

superstition.英释: a belief that some objects or actions are lucky or unlucky, or that they cause events to happen, based on old ideas of magic

entrepreneur.英释: someone who starts a new business or arranges business deals in order to make money, often in a way that involves financial risks

compensation.英释: money paid to someone because they have suffered injury or loss, or because something they own has been damaged

practitioner.中释: 开业者，从业者，执业医生
practitioner.英释: someone who works as a doctor or a lawyer

incidentally.英释: used to add more information to what you have just said, or to introduce a new subject that you have just thought of

acquaintance.英释: someone you know, but who is not a close friend

satisfaction.中释: 满意，满足；赔偿；乐事；赎罪
satisfaction.英释: a feeling of happiness or pleasure because you have achieved something or got what you wanted

thanksgiving.英释: an expression of thanks to God

introduction.中释: 介绍；引进；采用；入门；传入
introduction.英释: the act of bringing something into use for the first time

irrespective.中释: 无关的；不考虑的；不顾的

intermittent.中释: 间歇的；断断续续的；间歇性
intermittent.英释: stopping and starting often and for short periods

encyclopedia.英释: a book or cd, or a set of these, containing facts about many different subjects, or containing detailed facts about one subject

confidential.中释: 机密的；表示信任的；获信任的
confidential.英释: spoken or written in secret and intended to be kept secret

mathematical.中释: 数学的，数学上的；精确的

satisfactory.中释: 满意的；符合要求的；赎罪的
satisfactory.英释: something that is satisfactory seems good enough for you, or good enough for a particular situation or purpose

quantitative.英释: relating to amounts rather than to the quality or standard of something

complication.中释: 并发症；复杂；复杂化；混乱
complication.英释: a problem or situation that makes something more difficult to understand or deal with

transmission.中释: 传动装置，[机] 变速器；传递；传送；播送
transmission.英释: the process of sending out electronic signals, messages etc, using radio, television, or other similar equipment

contemporary.中释: 当代的；同时代的；属于同一时期的

metropolitan.中释: 大城市人；大主教；宗主国的公民

bibliography.英释: a list of all the books and articles used in preparing a piece of writing

conversation.中释: 交谈，会话；社交；交往，交际；会谈；（人与计算机的）人机对话
conversation.英释: an informal talk in which people exchange news, feelings, and thoughts

intelligible.中释: 可理解的；明了的；仅能用智力了解的
intelligible.英释: Something that is intelligible can be understood

instrumental.英释: a piece of music in which no voices are used, only instruments

headquarters.英释: the main building or offices used by a large company or organization

handkerchief.英释: a piece of cloth that you use for drying your nose or eyes

illustration.英释: a picture in a book, article etc, especially one that helps you to understand it

installation.英释: when someone fits a piece of equipment somewhere

commonwealth.英释: The commonwealth is an organization consisting of the United Kingdom and most of the countries that were previously under its rule

kindergarten.英释: a school for children aged two to five

surroundings.英释: the objects, buildings, natural things etc that are around a person or thing at a particular time

civilization.英释: a society that is well organized and developed, used especially about a particular society in a particular place or at a particular time

discriminate.英释: to treat a person or group differently from another in an unfair way

intersection.中释: 交叉；十字路口；交集；交叉点
intersection.英释: a place where roads, lines etc cross each other, especially where two roads meet

experimental.中释: 实验的；根据实验的；试验性的
experimental.英释: used for, relating to, or resulting from experiments

intelligence.中释: 智力,聪明;理解力；情报,消息,报导
intelligence.英释: the ability to learn, understand, and think about things

circumstance.英释: the conditions that affect a situation, action, event etc

congratulate.英释: to tell someone that you are happy because they have achieved something or because something nice has happened to them
